\begin_layout Itemize
In player number card rotation, starting with #1, players may act for one
 of:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Themselves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
One of their cousins.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A company they direct.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or pass.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Passing does not prevent that player from acting on a later turn in the
 same Stock Round.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
A player cannot pass in a Stock Round if one of their cousins is director
 of a company and can sell one or more shares of that company (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Overview-Cousins"

\end_inset

 & 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Selling-shares"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This process continues until all of the players in order do not do any of:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Fund a lobby or increase the funding of a lobby.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Increase the share-count of a company.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The Stock Round is then interrupted and any lobbies are resolved (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Resolving-lobbies"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The Stock Round then continues in player number card rotation, except that:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Lobby and share-count actions are no longer available in that Stock Round.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When players elect to pass in the Stock Round, they take the lowest numbered
 available player number card of the other colour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When players act in the Stock Round, they return any player number card
 of the other colour they have to the supply.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The player with the next larger number card of the other colour then swaps
 their card for the returned card, repeating as necessary for the other
 players such that the other player number cards show the order in which
 those players passed and ceased acting in the Stock Round.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The Stock Round ends when all the player number cards of the other colour
 have been taken (all players have passed in rotation).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Cousin and player purchases are limited to their available cash.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The Stock Round ends when all players pass in order.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If the players all pass in order before any lobbies are resolved:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The lobbies are resolved (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Resolving-lobbies"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Then the Stock Round continues until the players all pass in order for a
 second time.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
After the Stock Round:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The player number cards of the current colour are returned to the supply.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The player number cards of the other colour will determine the player order
 in the next Stock Round.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Stock prices of companies with shares in the bank pool are adjusted (see
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:SR-stock-price"

