\begin_layout Paragraph
Increase share-count 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:Increase-share-count"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A company director may increase the share-count of that company:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The company must have been floated in a prior Stock Round.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The available share-counts are shown in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Company-Sizes"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The following steps are done in order: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
If the company is a private company:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The director selects a currently available par price (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sec:Stock-Market"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Moves the private company's marker from the private track to the Stock Market
 at that stock price.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The stock price marker is placed below other stock price markers already
 at that price.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The director's private certificate is exchanged for a single share of the
 newly public company.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The company director selects the new larger share count (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Company-Sizes"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Additional shares are added to the company treasury until the total number
 of shares for the company in the treasury, player hands and the bank pool
 matches the new share-count (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Company-Sizes"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The director ensures that 40% of the company is bought from the company
 treasury, as a combination of previously held shares and shares now sold
 to players and cousins at the current stock price (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Buying-shares"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This may be any combination of players and cousins chosen at the director's
 discretion (and who must agree and buy those shares -- see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Buying-shares"

\end_inset

 & 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Negotiation-&-Holdings"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Control of the company may be transferred due to these purchases (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Company-directors"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Players currently holding shares of the company may sell them at this point,
